        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 5:54PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 554 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Gordo, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lake Tuscaloosa, Northport, Moores Bridge, Windham Springs, Samantha,
Flatwoods, Holt, Lake Harris, Stillman College, Lake Nicol, Echola,
Lake Lurleen State Park, Highway 69 Bridge, Tuscaloosa Amphitheater,
Bryant Denny Stadium, Tuscaloosa Regional Airport, Oliver Lock And
Dam, Elrod, Lake Tuscaloosa Dam, and University Mall.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
west central Alabama.</instruction>
